<br>
Elil searched for some strength, something do delay the orc.  The orc's huge weapon was rising above his head.  He let himself pass out.<br>
<br>
In that very same moment there was a warm feeling on his chest.  The feeling grew until it was an unbearable burning.  Elil woke up just as a huge beam of light burst from his neckless, slamming into Agaolite.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/unitetimehero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nitetimehero</A> at: 1/11/02 4:00:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=psychosoldier>Psycho Soldier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/11/02 11:55:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=82>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 2</span><hr size=1> To see and or hear a cry like this from a monster like this was a thought that was not to be thought of.  Elil assured himself that he now was dead, no living soul was to see this.<br>
<br>
The light that danced about the torching flames that was the charring flesh which once belonged to Agaolite was a fantastic savior to Elil.  What ever this light had been, when it struck this sad creature it made it's full wrath known.<br>
<br>
Falling to a defeated posture on his hands and knees, Agaolite gasped for breath.  He was not dead, but that elf might as well be.  This thought burned in the orc's mind.  He was not to be defeated, not like this, not now.<br>
<br>
Agaolite could not make out the elf any longer, perhaps his last eye had been scorched and withered, he could not tell nor cared.  Fury of rage was still in his veins, he'd nearly been bested...<br>
<br>
Standing he took his zambato again, unable to talk from the charring, he spat up blood and other bodily fluids in a distorted cry of pain and insanity.<br>
<br>
Resembling that of berserker more and more, Agaolite... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=psychosoldier>Psycho Soldier</A> at: 1/12/02 5:04:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrandxduke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GrandxDuke</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/12/02 12:12:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=83>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 2</span><hr size=1> Sonto creeps to a cave opening placing his right hand on the opening.  He rests breathing shallowly.  His hair hangs in front of his face and he is clearly in great distress.  Sweat pours down his brow and his pupils have narrowed down to pinpoints.  His eyes appear to be sunken in and his veins along his neck bulge.<br>
<br>
He quickly begins to gasp for air while his body fidgets.  He clasps his right wrist and almost appears to be trying to pull his arm off.  His body begins to spasm with his right arm, especially his hand, whipping about while his left arm struggles to keep them in control.  His right hand flares with light and quickly his glove is burned in a brilliant bright white light.  Presented to the world is a grotesque scare etched into his hand that burns bright.  With every fluctuation of the scare Sonto’s eyes flare up slightly.<br>
<br>
The runic carving in Sonto’s hand burns but with what is left of his rational mind at the moment he holds back cries of pain fearing to reveal his position.  With one final flash his eyes roll back and he falls to the ground.<br>
<br>
Sonto lies on the ground for a few minutes until finally he picks himself up.  As he stands his eyes roll back into position.  They appear to be glazed over and staring off into nothing.  Slowly Sonto walks into the cave after his prey . . .<br>
