<br>
Inhuman sounds spluttered from the mouth of the beast as it came.  Longsword met Zambato with an ear splitting crash.  The fighting continued until the ground was scorched black and nearbye trees were completely striped of their bark.<br>
<br>
These were no longer mere men, but titans.  The magic of Elil's pendant coursed through his body, and Agaolite was finally granted the power of his master.<br>
<br>
A swing of the zambato caused Elil to leap into the air.  As he came down his foot smashed Agaolite's cheek.  The two stood facing each other, both seeing more than eyes could ever give them.<br>
<br>
Longsword and zambato began to glow from the power of their champions.  Then they charged, Elil moving like the wind over the ground and Agaolite pounding as if he were one with it.  <br>
<br>
The zambato which saught Elil, instead found his longsword and was flung away.  With one powerful strike the full force of the pendant flowed through the sword, into Agaolite.  <br>
<br>
The fight was finally over.  The burning disappeared from his chest as he looked toward his destination.  He would have to find his horse, for it could no longer be tied up. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/unitetimehero.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nitetimehero</A> at: 1/12/02 8:05:14 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=psychosoldier>Psycho Soldier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/12/02 9:17:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=86>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 2</span><hr size=1> As Agaolite lied in his wretched vessel of a growing corpse he could manage nothing, his heart had been pierced by fire.<br>
<br>
Well nothing isn't quite the right thing to say, he could manage a strained thought.  Though these final thoughts were scattered and not of much importance.<br>
<br>
Perhaps if he had swung his weapon one way, or chewed the pendant off...<br>
<br>
Bah, it didn't matter.  If Agaolite was lucky he'd be able to come back some day in some way and exact his revenge.<br>
<br>
For now, as darkness loomed in his mind, his breath slowing, and all the limbs of his body went to a feelingness numb, Agaolite would just lie in quiet rubble; waiting for what ever may be... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=psychosoldier>Psycho Soldier</A> at: 1/12/02 9:23:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugrandxduke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GrandxDuke</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/12/02 9:35:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=87>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 2</span><hr size=1> As Elil walked away from the burned corpse that now matches its heart a shadow moves from tree to tree.  Move, that is the wrong word to use.  It more of disappears behind one tree then reappears behind another. This shadow makes its way near to the corpse making sure not to arise Elil’s attention.<br>
<br>
Once the shadow is sure that he will not be found he reveals himself.  It’s an imp.  It’s short and skinny with long pointy ears.  Its mouth is nearly as wide as its face.  He has narrow deep red eyes with little slits for pupils.  His clothing is somewhat of a cross between a jester and a ranger.  His attire is dark with mixes of blacks and browns save, for the gold jewelry in his ears.<br>
<br>
“Look what those brutes did to my creation.”<br>
<br>
The imp skips to the corpse and uses his entire body to pick up just the hand of morbid body, which is nearly as large as he is.<br>
<br>
“So much work gone to waste.  That monster just had to ruin his other eye, I could have made use of it.  Bah!  Away with the old and in with the new.  The new model should prove much more useful.”<br>
<br>
The Imp looks about for a few seconds and then skips off towards the caves.<br>
<br>
“Knowing the other two they’ll end up the same way.”<br>
<br>
With a grunt the imp disappears into shadows and once again seems to disappear behind one tree and inexplicably appear behind another one.<br>
