“You look good.”  Cryrid’s words are sarcastically spoken.  His voice is rough as his body begins to lack more vital tissues.  His body is now a mass of bones with varying amounts of flesh hanging off at key points such as the elbows and the base of the head.  Cryrid is no longer a handsome knight but a zombie or maybe some other dark entity from behind the grave.  It would truly be horrible to think of this creature as part of the living world.<br>
<br>
Sonto looks up slowly, he appears to be worn.  His constitute is frail as his right hand slowly rises.  Van Eyck and Cameron struggle to move though an unforeseen force binds their feet keeping them still.<br>
<br>
“You feel that?”  Van Eyck speaks softly trying to keep the words to his traveling companion only.<br>
<br>
“Aye, it’s not normal.  Fortunately the mage’s attention is not on us; we might just be an audience.”<br>
<br>
“You aren’t supposed to be here,” Sonto’s words are weakly spoken.<br>
<br>
“Validus couldn’t trust you.  You raise arms against me?  Your magic isn’t effective against the dead.  My body holds no allegiance to any element.  Validus will hear of you betrayal.”<br>
<br>
“Let go of the girl.”<br>
<br>
“She could be the one Validus is looking for.”<br>
<br>
Sonto walks up slowly to the two.  Open palm out he places his right hand within inches of Cryrid face.<br>
<br>
“I dare you.”<br>
<br>
With a flash the insignia on Sonto’s right hand flashes.  His hand curls into a fist and pushes forward into Cryrid face.  The punch is awkward with only Sonto’s arm moving and the rest of his body still.  Cryrid form is blown away leaving a shaken Caprice.<br>
<br>
“Leave.”<br>
<br>
Caprice stumbles over a large rock hidden in the dark and makes her way to her entranced warriors.<br>
<br>
Cryrid gets up appearing to have being hurt little, though his head does hang to the right slightly.<br>
<br>
“What’s the matter?”<br>
<br>
“I don’t kill women.”<br>
<br>
“But cities of elves?”<br>
<br>
The insignia on Sonto’s hand flares bright lighting the cave’s walls- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uinfestedmatrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>infestedmatrix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(1/25/02 11:00:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=94>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Polykarbon Roleplaying, Chapter 2</span><hr size=1> Timohty was inturrupted by a loud soud only heared through his ears.  Moments passed and he looked up at Elil.  &quot;Cryrid, he has betrayed us.&quot; he spoke. <br>
 Just then Timothy began to glow white.  A flash of light came upon his body.  His armor began to change into thick shiny crome iron.  It appeared all down his body, coming from no where.  In a flash, his sword was replaced by a large object with a long barrel.  His helmet turned chrome pulled over his forhead.  And with another flash of light, large wings appeared out of his back.  Elil stood in amazement of the sight.<br>
